**Explanation:** The `debounce` function delays the execution of a given function until after a specified amount of time has passed since the last time the debounced function was invoked.

```javascript
// Debounce function
function debounce(func, wait) {
  let timeout;
  return function executedFn(...args) {
    const context = this;
    clearTimeout(timeout);
    timeout = setTimeout(() => func.apply(context, args), wait);
  };
}

// Usage example:
const heavyFunction = () => {
  console.log("Heavy function executed");
};

const debouncedHeavyFunction = debounce(heavyFunction, 300); // Debounce heavyFunction with a delay of 300ms

// Call debouncedHeavyFunction multiple times within 300ms
for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  debouncedHeavyFunction();
}

// After 300ms, "Heavy function executed" will be logged to the console only once.
```
